I have posted a quick review of the Three Days Grace performance at this year's Ed Fest. Please head on over and check it out (pictures to come... digital camera is on my list of things to purchase, recommedations?) Also I met up with today to pick up my entrance pass for Friday. I was kind of nervous at first while telling my coworkers where I was goin, but as I rode the bus to meet up I got more relaxed and when I saw at the door I got excited :D I might not have totally shown it, but I have issues with showing emotions or something or other. I was thinking about it later that maybe I should have mentioned my hair colour, since I got it dyed a few weeks ago (tells you how much I pay attention to my own hair and style). It is a shame that we couldn't talk more and that my cell rang (it was my mother, btw), but we shall chat lots when we go out for drinks and a movie :D
For my semi half assed account of tonight's A.F.I. concert please check out my media review blog. Pictures to come once I get them developed :)

I am very super extra pleased to announce the opening of my newest fanlisting for Captain Canada himself (and on Canada Day to boot!) for Ryan Smyth of the Edmonton Oilers! Please go and check out Pure Grit and join if you are a fan of this awesome hockey player.

The always lovely and awesome has created a fanlisting for me... There are people who are fans of me? What is wrong with you people!! :P Anyways, I already told her but a big thanks and hugs to *hugs* On another note, YAY for hockey. We are not dead, we are still in the finals Whee! *sits down, toddles off to wash paint off body*

I would like to announce the launch of my newest site, Diligence which is a now small fansite dedicated to the lead guitarist from My Chemical Romance, Ray Toro . So please go on and check it out and tell me if you find anything amiss or if you have any contributions to make. Also, WOOOOOOOOOOOOOOT! We are going to the Stanley Cup Final!!! Wooooooooo!

You scored 47 Mass, 37 Electronegativity, 54 Metal, and 0 Radioactivity!
I like to think of you as the miracle worker in The Princess Bride... you can do anything and you do it for the betterment of society. Just because you can raise the dead and make flying wagons and stuff doesn't mean that you show off about it though. You are capable of forming bizarre webs of relationships in which individuals are accomplices, lovers, coworkers, and so on all at once. I once saw you hanging out at the center of a cycloheptatriene... it was completely freakish and bizarre, and I'm not sure I've known what to think of you since. But hey, to each their own. Oh, and stay away from the carbon monoxide... you suck that stuff up.

Your brain: 15% interpersonal, 20% visual, 25% verbal, and 40% mathematical!
Congratulations on being 100% smart! The above score breaks down what kind of thinking you most enjoy doing. It says nothing about how good you are at any one, just how interested you are in each, relatively. A substantial difference in scores between two people means, conclusively, that they are different kinds of thinkers.

Matching Summary: Each of us has different tastes. Still, I offer the following advice, which I think is obvious:

  1. Don't date someone if your interpersonal percentages differ by more than 50%.
  2. Don't be friends with someone if your verbal percentages differ by more than 60%.
  3. Don't have sex with someone if their math percentage is over 50%.

Okay well I decided to upgrade my weblog from Greymatter to Wordpress, so obviously I had to make a new layout to go with it :) Anyways, here it is, I call it 'Bring me the Disco King' and it features the lovely David Bowie.

Anyone on my friends list using Frienditto please inform me and remove me from your friends list as I appreciate my privacy and do not want my private entries posted on a public website. For more information on Frienditto please click here or here.

Okay so last Friday Aaron came by and dropped off his Valentine's gift for me and it was The Chronicles of Narnia 1965-1974 Puffin/Penguin printing with Pauline Baynes' artwork on the covers.  Let me say that these are the covers that I fell in love with as a child and now after finally being able to read the full series after... 14 years I really have the urge to write Narnia fanfic.  My hand itches when I grab my coding pen at work, but I have to supress it to complete my work or get fired... or put on probation.  So I think that while I am not outside enjoying the weather this weekend (10 C on Sat and 13C on Sun) I will try writing down some plotlines and character outlines.

*pimps her new DV related icon* Okay first off I received 's card earlier this week and yay for stars! Next I have 's gift sitting righ tbeside me waiting to be stuffed with tissue paper to prevent breakage/injury/etc. Do not be fooled by the box that it comes in as it was the only box I could find that was big enough to hold your gift. It will prolly go out next week if all goes well with my dad and at work. All the mix CDs are sitting right besid emy computer as well and as soon as I find out where our accounts receiveable clerk bought her CD envelopes with the padding on them I will send them out. I have gifts for and over by the gift to and they will all go out at the same time. Now for 's gift I am trying to wait until I get my paypal account because you might not recognize my boyfriend's name and relate it to me. Now for and I am going to go downtown or to the southside to find your gifts because I have absolutely no clue as to what I am getting you. Now back to my life... my life away from LJ *shockgasp* I have taken up doing embroidery this past week as I needed to find a hobby other than LJ and the net in general. So far I remember most of the stitches that I knew from 6 or so years back. The work week is almost up thankfully and then I will be free to hopefully watch Spooks/MI-5 on Friday night if Aaron has to work Saturday morning and does not pick me up. *crosses fingers* I love him dearly but I also love Spooks/MI-5. Other than that I have been reading through the Night World series and really understanding them a bit better than I did when I was a teenager who had never been involved in a relationship. I also am still reading the X manga that sent me and I found a translation guide so it makes it that much better :) So that is pretty much all I have to say... I absolutely love Cozy Heart Penguin I even brought him to work to show off to my coworkers :D *loves her new friend*  And I am starting to read the X/1999 manga you sent me. From 1. Put your birth month in an entry. 2. Strike out anything that doesn't apply to you. 3. Bold the things that best apply to you. 4. Put all twelve months under a livejournal cut SEPTEMBER: Suave and compromising. Careful, cautious and organized. Likes to point out people's mistakes. Likes to criticize. Stubborn. Quiet but able to talk well. Calm and cool. Kind and sympathetic. Concerned and detailed. Loyal but not always honest. Does work well. Very confident. Sensitive. Tries to be generous. Good memory. Clever and knowledgeable. Loves to look for information. Must control oneself when criticizing. Able to motivate oneself. Understanding. Fun to be around. Secretive. Loves sports, leisure and traveling. Hardly shows emotions. Tends to bottle up feelings. Very choosy, especially in relationships. Systematic. JANUARY: Stubborn and hard-hearted. Ambitious and serious. Loves to teach and be taught. Always looking at people's flaws and weaknesses. Likes to criticize. Hardworking and productive. Smart, neat and organized. Sensitive and has deep thoughts. Knows how to make others happy. Quiet unless excited or tensed. Rather reserved. Highly attentive. Resistant to illnesses but prone to colds. Romantic but has difficulties expressing love. Loves children. Loyal. Has great social abilities yet easily jealous. Very stubborn and money cautious. FEBRUARY: Abstract thoughts. Loves reality and abstract. Intelligent and clever. Changing personality. Attractive. Sexy. Temperamental. Quiet, shy and humble. Honest and loyal. Determined to reach goals. Loves freedom. Rebellious when restricted. Loves aggressiveness. Too sensitive and easily hurt. Gets angry really easily but does not show it. Dislikes unnecessary things. Loves making friends but rarely shows it. Daring and stubborn. Ambitious. Realizing dreams and hopes. Sharp. Loves entertainment and leisure. Romantic on the inside not outside. Superstitious and ludicrous. Spendthrift.
